  "text": "Cells and culture conditions. HT29 clone 19A is a permanent subclone derived from the carcinoma cell line HT29 treated with sodium butyrate [CITATION_1] . The cells were grown in tissue culture flasks with Dulbecco modified Eaglemedium (Gibco BRL, Eggenstein, Germany) supplemented with 10% fetal calf serum (FCS) and 1% penicillin/streptomycin at 37°C in a humidified incubator (5% CO 2 /95% air). For this study we used passages 20-50.",
